FX Regime Lab — Cursor Rules
Read TASK.md at the start of every session before anything else.
Then read only the docs/ files listed in TASK.md for the current task.
Never read all docs at once.
Session discipline

Read TASK.md first. Always.
State which files you will modify before modifying any file.
Complete one task fully before starting another.
If scope creep appears mid-task, note it in TASK.md under "Discovered issues" and finish the current task first.
After completing a task, print: DONE — [task name] — [files modified] — [files created]

What to read for each domain

Frontend task → docs/FRONTEND_ARCHITECTURE.md + docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md
Database/query task → docs/DATABASE_SCHEMA.md
Pipeline task → docs/PIPELINE_REFERENCE.md
Signal/regime task → docs/SIGNAL_DEFINITIONS.md
New feature → docs/FEATURE_REGISTRY.md + docs/PHASES.md
Unclear → docs/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md then decide

Hard rules (never violate)

Never use Chart.js, ECharts, Plotly, or Recharts anywhere in web/
Never write supabase.from() inside components, pages, or hooks — queries.ts only
Never modify *.py files unless TASK.md explicitly says to modify Python
Never modify workers/site-entry.js unless TASK.md explicitly says to
Never modify .github/workflows/ unless TASK.md explicitly says to
Never use inline styles in web/ — Tailwind only
Never use any TypeScript type — strict mode enforced
Never hardcode pair names, regime labels, or route paths — use lib/constants/
Server components → lib/supabase/server.ts
Client components → lib/supabase/client.ts
Every new page route needs loading.tsx and error.tsx siblings
TradingView Lightweight Charts v5 is the only chart library

Token efficiency rules

Read only the files relevant to the current task
Do not re-read files already read in this session
Do not print file contents unless asked
Do not explain what you are about to do — just do it
Do not summarise what you just did at length — print the DONE line and stop
Do not ask clarifying questions if TASK.md and the relevant doc answer them
If genuinely unclear, ask one specific question, not multiple

Code quality rules

TypeScript strict — no any, no ts-ignore, no type assertions without comment
Every function needs a return type annotation
No console.log in production code — use proper error handling
Wrap all Supabase calls in try/catch
Handle null/undefined from all Supabase responses before using data
images.unoptimized must stay true in next.config.js (Cloudflare Pages requirement)
export const runtime = 'edge' required on dynamic routes and API routes
compatibility_date must stay 2025-01-01 or later in wrangler.toml
